This article is a Presidential Memorandum from June 2, 2010, regarding the delegation of authority to appoint commissioned officers of the Ready Reserve Corps of the Public Health Service. The President assigns the Secretary of Health and Human Services the functions of appointing commissioned officers of the Ready Reserve Corps, as specified in section 203 of the Public Health Service Act. This authority is limited to individuals who were offered employment for appointment and active duty in the Reserve Corps after March 23, 2010, but were not on active duty on that date. It also includes individuals selected for the 2010 Commissioned Officer Student Training and Extern Program. The authority cannot be delegated further, and the memorandum is to be published in the Federal Register.